node.text: Introducing Sipping With, a new series hosted by Contributing Editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker), who’s taking us behind the bar at world-renowned restaurants, hotels, and resorts to see how the best in the business craft specialty cocktails. On this episode, Sean visits @themarkhotelny, where Bartender Ken Ziegler shows us how to make a ginger margarita — a fresh take on the classic. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Learn How One of the Best Hotels in NYC Makes Its Signature Margarita

node.text: In the latest installment of our Walk With T+L series, you can tour Disney World's Magic Kingdom with an Imagineer and uncover the design secrets you might have missed during your last visit. We’ll visit the exclusive Cinderella Castle Suite, the Beauty and the Beast-themed Be Our Guest Restaurant, and so much more. Come along as we get an inside look at how Disney “makes magic real” — the theme of the Magic Kingdom.

node.title: Uncover the Magic Kingdom's Design Secrets With a Disney Imagineer

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: the island of Amorgos, Greece. The Greek Islands are on just about everyone's bucket list. But like many of the world’s most photogenic destinations, over-tourism has become a real issue. Luckily, there are more than 200 inhabited islands in Greece, meaning you can get all of the beauty and none the crowds on some of the lesser-known islands, like Amorgos. Come along! Tour by @_thebluewalk

node.title: This Greek Island Has All of the Beauty and None of the Crowds

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: Paris, France. A city that needs no introduction, Paris may as well be synonymous with food, culture, fashion, and architecture. Despite being a bucket-list destination for millions of people, the French capital still holds plenty of hidden secrets beyond the Eiffel Tower and world-class museums. Join us on this walking tour to see for yourself. Tour by @walkstours

node.title: Jet Off to Paris From the Comfort of Your Home on This Virtual Walking Tour

Tour by @manumissiontour

node.text:
"THE BIG 5-0! Well, fifty years looks good on you, Travel + Leisure! Hard to believe this iconic brand is celebrating a golden anniversary in 2021, a year when the travel industry has never needed more love and support.
.
I love to think that at T+L, our words have helped shape and inspire countless trips. Amazing trips. And that our travel images have grabbed your attention, made you stop, stare, and dream for a bit, even if you couldn’t hop on a plane right that second. 
.
We have produced hundreds of covers since 1971, admittedly some better than others. One thing I’ve noticed, spending months looking at back issues: As the decades progressed, certain styles emerged. Certain trends. T+L covers are actually a documentary of our world, and how we moved through it as travelers." -T+L Editor in Chief @jacquigiff
.
Throughout this week, we'll look back on the past five decades of T+L covers and explore what they can teach us about how travel has evolved. Check our feed every day this week for a new post, and join us in celebrating 50 years of T+L!
